"title": "8618: prayerfulness",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "8618",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>An attitude by which a constant relationship between God and believers is developed.</p>\n<h2>Prayerfulness is a way of life</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke2:37\">LUK 2:37</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps5:3\">PSA 5:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps55:17\">PSA 55:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps109:4\">PSA 109:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan6:10-Dan6:11\">DAN 6:10–6:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan6:13\">DAN 6:13</a></p>\n<h2>Prayerfulness arises from a desire to be with God</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps130:5-Ps130:6\">PSA 130:5–130:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps42:1-Ps42:4\">PSA 42:1–42:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps84:1-Ps84:2\">PSA 84:1–84:2</a></p>\n<h2>Prayerfulness arises from an awareness of need that can only be met by God</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim5:5\">1TI 5:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps86:1\">PSA 86:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps105:4\">PSA 105:4</a></p>\n<h2>Prayerfulness demonstrates a continuing trust in God</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John15:5-John15:8\">JHN 15:5–15:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps63:1-Ps63:8\">PSA 63:1–63:8</a></p>\n<h2>Prayerfulness involves a heart that is right with God</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa1:15-Isa1:17\">ISA 1:15–1:17</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt6:7\">MAT 6:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark12:40\">MRK 12:40</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke20:47\">LUK 20:47</a></p>\n<h2>Prayerfulness involves the need to be alert</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:41\">MAT 26:41</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:38\">MRK 14:38</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:40\">LUK 22:40</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mic7:7\">MIC 7:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke21:36\">LUK 21:36</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col4:2\">COL 4:2</a></p>\n<h2>Prayerfulness needs to be maintained especially in difficult circumstances</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke18:1\">LUK 18:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hab3:16-Hab3:19\">HAB 3:16–3:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts16:25\">ACT 16:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess5:17\">1TH 5:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet4:7\">1PE 4:7</a></p>\n<h2>Examples of people whose prayerfulness proved effective</h2>\n<h3>Hannah, who prayed for a child</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam1:20\">1SA 1:20</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa1:10-Isa1:18\">ISA 1:10–1:18</a></p>\n<h3>Elijah, an ordinary man who prayed</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas5:17-Jas5:18\">JAS 5:17–5:18</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs17:1\">1KI 17:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs18:41-1Kgs18:46\">1KI 18:41–18:46</a></p>\n<h3>Nehemiah, a man who discovered God's plan through prayer</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh1:4\">NEH 1:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh1:5-Neh1:11\">NEH 1:5–1:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh2:4-Neh2:5\">NEH 2:4–2:5</a></p>\n<h3>David, sustained through trials</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam30:6\">1SA 30:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam22:1-2Sam22:4\">2SA 22:1–22:4</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps18:1-Ps18:3\">PSA 18:1–18:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps3:1-Ps3:8\">PSA 3:1–3:8</a></p>\n<h3>Daniel, whose patience in prayer was rewarded</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan10:12\">DAN 10:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan9:1-Dan9:19\">DAN 9:1–9:19</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ, who perfectly trusted his Father</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb5:7\">HEB 5:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke5:16\">LUK 5:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John11:41-John11:42\">JHN 11:41–11:42</a></p>\n<h3>The early church, which was founded upon prayer</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts1:14\">ACT 1:14</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:42\">ACT 2:42</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts4:23-Acts4:31\">ACT 4:23–4:31</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts6:4\">ACT 6:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts12:5\">ACT 12:5</a></p>\n<h3>Paul, who prayed for all the churches which he founded or visited</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col1:9\">COL 1:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom1:9-Rom1:10\">ROM 1:9–1:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph1:16\">EPH 1:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil1:4\">PHP 1:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess3:10\">1TH 3:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Thess1:11\">2TH 1:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim1:3\">2TI 1:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phlm1:4\">PHM 1:4</a></p>",
